gomodel:SYNGO_1753  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: This study used a transgenic mouse model to test synaptic roles of SynCAM 1. Figs. 2A,B and 2F,G show that the overexpression of SynCAM 1 in excitatory neurons in vivo is sufficient to increase the number of excitatory synapses and of dendritic spines, a morphological correlate of excitatory synapses. The results in Fig. 5E demonstrate that this increase is lost when SynCAM 1 overexpression is turned off. These results support an instructive role of SynCAM 1 in the induction of excitatory synapses.. Experimental description: - This study used transgenic and knock-out mouse models\n- Personal communication with author on the species of the over-expressed SynCAM1: \"We used a SynCAM 1 I cloned from a mouse brain library\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1753" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

